Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Common Utilities Module

Provides shared utility functions used across the advanced stdlib modules.
This centralizes common functions to eliminate duplication and ensure 
consistent behavior across the advanced features.

Features:
- Time and timestamp utilities
- Collection copying utilities  
- Random string generation
- Common data structure operations
- Production-ready implementations with error handling

This module serves as the single source of truth for utility functions
that were previously duplicated across multiple advanced modules.
:End Note

Import "time" as Time

Note: Time and Timestamp Functions
Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Returns current time in seconds since epoch
    Try:
        Return Time.time
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback to fixed timestamp if time module unavailable
        Return 1234567890.0

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Alias for get_current_time for backward compatibility
    Return get_current_time

Note: Collection Utility Functions
Process called "copy_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns List[Any]:
    Note: Creates a shallow copy of the input list
    Let copy be list containing
    For each item in list:
        Add item to copy
    Return copy

Process called "copy_dictionary" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Creates a shallow copy of the input dictionary
    Let copy be dictionary containing
    For each key in dict:
        Set copy[key] to dict[key]
    Return copy

Note: Random String Generation
Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generates a random alphanumeric string of specified length
    Try:
        Import "random" as Random
        Let chars be "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789"
        Let result be ""
        
        For i from 0 to length:
            Let random_index be Random.randint with 0 as min and length of chars minus 1 as max
            Set result to result plus chars[random_index]
        
        Return result
    Catch error:
        Note: Fallback implementation using timestamp-based generation
        Let timestamp be get_current_time
        Let base_string be "random_" plus timestamp plus "_" plus length
        Return base_string

Note: Additional Utility Functions
Process called "generate_unique_id" returns String:
    Note: Generates a unique identifier using timestamp
    Let timestamp be get_current_time
    Return "id_" plus timestamp

Process called "create_empty_list" returns List[Any]:
    Note: Creates an empty list for initialization
    Return list containing

Process called "create_empty_dictionary" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Creates an empty dictionary for initialization
    Return dictionary containing

Note: String and Format Utilities
Process called "format_timestamp" that takes timestamp as Float returns String:
    Note: Formats timestamp as readable string
    Return "timestamp_" plus timestamp

Process called "safe_string_concat" that takes parts as List[String] returns String:
    Note: Safely concatenates string parts with error handling
    Try:
        Let result be ""
        For each part in parts:
            Set result to result plus part
        Return result
    Catch error:
        Return "concat_error"